cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB

This paper deals with predicting the formation of anchor links between different social networks, which involves modeling social factors that may affect a user's decision to join a new network. This falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). The use of meta-paths and machine learning techniques for prediction also aligns with the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and digital libraries (cs.DL). However, since the paper primarily focuses on social network analysis, we consider cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the most likely sub-category.
